{
  "text": "Proposition 5.3 generalizes [CITATION_1] characterization of the nucleolus. The equivalence between (1) and (2) is proved similarly as in the classical case. The equivalence between (2) and (3) which is an immediate consequence of Farkas' lemma occurs as a special case of Lemma 2.1 of [CITATION_2] and is, e.g., explicitly proved by [CITATION_3] . \u2022 the unrestricted reconfirmation property (RCP free ) if the restriction of \u03c3 to \u0393 \u2032 \u2229 \u0393 free satisfies RCP.",
